<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE7FE6948A75251FE2BF8D1" pageId="425" pageNumber="426" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FE7FE6948A75251FCC7F90D" blockId="425.[151,1437,1405,1970]" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE7FE6948A75251FE09FA65" bold="true" box="[151,428,1405,1430]" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FE7FE694ABB5251FCBCFA65" box="[651,793,1405,1429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="425" pageNumber="426" unit="mm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Totally testaceous, except petiole black and metasoma black-brown. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 8:5:11:5:5:4.5:4.5:4.5:4.5:8. Head excavated, shiny, sculptured by hardly visible irregular striae; frontal line incomplete, not present in anterior half of face; occipital carina absent; POL = 3; OL = 2; OOL = 7. Palpal formula: 5/2. Pronotum shiny, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, sculptured by few longitudinal striae, without lateral pointed apophyses. Metanotum flat, shiny, transversely striate, hollow behind scutellum, with lateral regions very prominent and rounded (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE7FE69499C5179FD8DF99D" box="[428,552,1621,1645]" captionStart="PLATE 133" captionStartId="426.[151,234,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[187,1421,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-71@426.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="426" captionText="PLATE 133. A. Lateral view. Length 3.0 mm. B, D. Chelae. C. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, dorsal view. A, B. Gonatopus asiaticus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1987a). Scale bar 0.15 mm for B, 0.54 mm for C and 0.19 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278842/files/figure.png" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">Plate 133C</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, with posterior surface transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 15:3:4:10:15. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE7FE694BC251B1FBD7F945" box="[1010,1138,1693,1717]" captionStart="PLATE 133" captionStartId="426.[151,234,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[187,1421,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-71@426.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="426" captionText="PLATE 133. A. Lateral view. Length 3.0 mm. B, D. Chelae. C. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, dorsal view. A, B. Gonatopus asiaticus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1987a). Scale bar 0.15 mm for B, 0.54 mm for C and 0.19 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278842/files/figure.png" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">Plate 133D</figureCitation>
) with one large subapical tooth and one row of four–five lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE7FE694B9351EDFB81F929" box="[931,1060,1729,1753]" captionStart="PLATE 133" captionStartId="426.[151,234,1920,1943]" captionTargetBox="[187,1421,226,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-71@426.[151,1436,195,1898]" captionTargetPageId="426" captionText="PLATE 133. A. Lateral view. Length 3.0 mm. B, D. Chelae. C. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, dorsal view. A, B. Gonatopus asiaticus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). C, D. G.indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1987a). Scale bar 0.15 mm for B, 0.54 mm for C and 0.19 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278842/files/figure.png" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">Plate 133D</figureCitation>
) with two rows of about 11–13 lamellae; distal apex with about six lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FE7FE6948F75025FE2BF8D1" blockId="425.[151,1437,1405,1970]" box="[199,398,1801,1825]" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE7FE6948F75025FEAEF8D1" bold="true" box="[199,267,1801,1825]" pageId="425" pageNumber="426">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
